casebody.data:
HARPER v. MICHIGAN. No. 1103,

Misc.

Decided June 17, 1968. Frank J. Kelley, Attorney General of Michigan, Robert A. Derengoski, Solicitor General, and Stewart H. Freeman, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. Per Curiam.

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.
